---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Sustainability — Seamless™ Engineered Timbers"
  description="Locally sourced, carbon-negative, plant-based, biodegradable. Seamless timbers come from responsibly managed forests in British Columbia."
>

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 border-b border-line" style="padding-top: 6rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-6">Sustainability</div>
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 leading-[0.95] max-w-3xl">
      Wood has always been<br />
      <span class="italic text-cedar">the right answer.</span>
    </h1>
  </section>

  <!-- PILLARS STRIP -->
  <div class="border-b border-line">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 divide-x divide-line">
        <div class="py-6 px-4 first:pl-0">
          <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-1">Fiber source</div>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm">British Columbia</div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-6 px-4">
          <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-1">Carbon profile</div>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm">Carbon negative</div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-6 px-4">
          <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-1">Material type</div>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm">Plant-based · Renewable</div>
        </div>
        <div class="py-6 px-4">
          <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-1">End of life</div>
          <div class="font-medium text-sm">Biodegradable</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- THE ARGUMENT -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-b border-line">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-20 items-start">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow mb-4">The case for wood</div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 leading-[1.05] mb-6">
          The same logic applies<br />
          <span class="italic text-cedar">at every scale.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-smoke leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          When you choose a paper bag over plastic, or a paper straw instead of a plastic one,
          you're making a conscious decision about the kind of future you want to support.
          Building and remodeling are no different.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every post, every beam, every timber is a choice between renewable and non-renewable —
          between a material that sequesters carbon throughout its service life and one that
          emitted carbon getting there. We think that choice should be easy to make.
        </p>
        <p>
          Extending your commitment to renewable materials from the grocery store to the
          job site isn't idealism. It's consistency.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY WOOD -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-b border-line">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Why wood</div>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 mb-12">
      Four reasons it's the right call.
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8">
      <div class="border-t border-line pt-4">
        <div class="text-sm font-medium text-cedar mb-2">01 / Plant-based</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          Wood is grown, not mined or synthesized. It's a renewable resource on a human timescale —
          the same species we harvest today will be standing again within a generation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-line pt-4">
        <div class="text-sm font-medium text-cedar mb-2">02 / Carbon negative</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          Trees absorb CO₂ as they grow and lock it into the fiber. A wood post stores that carbon
          for the life of the building. Steel and concrete can't say the same — they emit carbon
          to produce.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-line pt-4">
        <div class="text-sm font-medium text-cedar mb-2">03 / Responsibly managed</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          Our fiber comes from British Columbia's managed forest system — one of the most
          regulated in the world. Harvest is paired with replanting. The forest doesn't disappear;
          it cycles.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-line pt-4">
        <div class="text-sm font-medium text-cedar mb-2">04 / Biodegradable</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          At the end of its service life, wood returns to the earth. No microplastics,
          no inert landfill mass, no toxic leachate. It came from the ground; it goes back.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR FIBER -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-b border-line">
    <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Our fiber</div>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 mb-3">
      BC wood. Managed forests.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-smoke mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      Every Seamless product traces back to a specific region of British Columbia.
      We know where the fiber comes from because that's the only way to stand behind what we build.
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="border border-line p-8">
        <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-2">Seamless Fascia Post</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">Northern &amp; Interior British Columbia</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          SPF — Spruce Pine Fir — sourced from Northern and Interior BC managed forest systems.
          Dense, consistent grain. Engineered into a hollow-core profile that carries structural
          loads with less fiber than solid stock.
        </p>
        <a href="/products/seamless-fascia-post" class="inline-block mt-6 eyebrow hover:text-cedar transition-colors">
          View product →
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="border border-line p-8">
        <div class="eyebrow text-ash mb-2">Seamless Cedar Timbers</div>
        <div class="text-xl font-medium mb-3">Coastal British Columbia</div>
        <p class="text-smoke leading-relaxed">
          Coastal Western Red Cedar from BC's coastal managed forests. Naturally rot-resistant,
          harvested responsibly, and engineered to reduce surface checking — so nothing goes to
          waste on site.
        </p>
        <a href="/products/seamless-cedar-timbers" class="inline-block mt-6 eyebrow hover:text-cedar transition-colors">
          View product →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SEAMLESS EFFICIENCY ANGLE -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-b border-line">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-20 items-start">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow mb-4">Engineered efficiency</div>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 leading-[1.05]">
          Less fiber.<br />
          <span class="italic text-cedar">More product.</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-smoke leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The hollow-core construction at the center of every Seamless timber isn't just
          a weight advantage — it's a materials story. Each cubic foot of BC fiber goes further
          than it would in a solid-sawn post.
        </p>
        <p>
          You get full-sawn dimensions, structural performance, and a finished appearance
          without the volume of fiber that solid stock requires. That's better for your build
          schedule and better for the forest.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-medium tracking-tighter-2 mb-4">
      Spec something you can <span class="italic text-cedar">stand behind.</span>
    </h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-smoke max-w-xl mb-8">
      Renewable material, responsible sourcing, engineered to last.
      Talk to our team about putting Seamless into your next project.
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/products" class="btn-primary">See the products →</a>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary">Talk to us</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
